<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF376A88FA5B9EF918AFB18D" pageId="204" pageNumber="966" type="description">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF376A88FA5B9EF918AFB18D" blockId="204.[1447,2654,2208,3145]" pageId="204" pageNumber="966">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFF376A88FA5B9EF918A4B38F" bold="true" box="[1447,1700,2208,2237]" pageId="204" pageNumber="966">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head—body 
<quantity id="036C9B1BFF376A88F89E9EF919C9B38F" box="[1890,1993,2208,2237]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.2" pageId="204" pageNumber="966" unit="mm" value="42.0">42 mm</quantity>
, tail 
<quantity id="036C9B1BFF376A88F7E99EF9167BB38F" box="[2069,2171,2208,2237]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.7" pageId="204" pageNumber="966" unit="mm" value="37.0">37 mm</quantity>
, ear 12- 
<quantity id="036C9B1BFF376A88F70F9EF91749B38F" box="[2291,2377,2208,2237]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="204" pageNumber="966" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
, hindfoot 
<quantity id="036C9B1BFF376A88F6199EF91456B38F" box="[2533,2646,2208,2237]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="204" pageNumber="966" unit="mm" value="6.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="6.0">6-7 mm</quantity>
, forearm 35-38- 
<quantity id="036C9B1BFF376A88F97C9E9A18D6B3D6" box="[1664,1750,2243,2276]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="204" pageNumber="966" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
. Dorsal pelage is brownish chestnut; venteris light brown. Ears are comparatively short, and tragus is relatively short at a little less than one-half the ear length, with straight anterior border and lower one-third being widest. Wing attaches to metatarsus offirst toe, and calcar is unkeeled. Baculum is only c. 
<quantity id="036C9B1BFF376A88F62D9F181455B268" box="[2513,2645,2369,2394]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="0.0" pageId="204" pageNumber="966" unit="mm" value="22.5" valueMax="45.0" valueMin="0.0">0-45 mm</quantity>
, straight, narrow, bluntly pointed distally, and slightly widened gradually to base; there is reduced urethral groove on bottom of basal one-half consisting of an oval depression. Forehead is distinctly elevated above low rostrum; sagittal crest is barely developed, and lambdoidalcrest isvisible laterally but weakly developed; C' is short, barely exceeding P* in height; P? is small, about two-thirds height of P* and one-half to twothirds the crown area but in tooth row; C,is also small, being shorter than P; P, and P, are small, with P, being one-half to two-thirds P, height; and M, is always nyctalodont, whereas M, is nyctalodont or seminyctalodont, and M, is almost always myotodont, rarely nyctalodont.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
